column1: Who will win the 2017 Academy Award for Actress in a Leading Role?
column5: ['Isabelle Huppert (Elle)', 'Ruth Negga (Loving)', 'Natalie Portman (Jackie)', 'Emma Stone (La La Land)', 'Meryl Streep (Florence Foster Jenkins)']
column11: The 89th Academy AwardsÂ® take place on Sunday, February 26. Confused? Check our FAQ or ask us for help.

column6: Based on La La Land's popularity and fan base, I'd say that Emma Stone has the best chance for the award. Meryl Streep in consistently good in movies, so I think she has the next best chance. Also, La La Land has swept up a ton of other awards since it's release just a few months ago, so there's awards momentum for that film.
20 points from NP to ES as move toward consensus.
Same reasons for alterations as other Oscars predictions
Slight lean to Stone. SAG is a big get. Need Huppert in case Portman/Stone split the vote for younger actress. Streep is in a comedy, and those can't win.

Once again, I relied on averages of the wisdom of the crowd from both GJP and Goldderby (I did not weight the sites, as I do not know which is more or less reliable. I also considered input from FiveThirtyEight, and the fact that Emma Stone won the Screen Actors Guild. I also think I have an advantage not predicting common percentages such as 5%, 10%, 20%, 25% etc.
Other awards and twitter predict that emma stone is a little ahead of Natalie Portman and Isabelle Huppert
The fact that Streep was nominated over Amy Adams seems to give her some momentum.
Stone gives the best performance,but Huppert and Portman seem to be getting the love.
